## Output File Naming

**Output file:** `{short_title}_{YYYYMMDD}_claude_editor_letter.tex`

Use same short_title and timestamp (YYYYMMDD) as the referee reports.

---

## Editor Letter Template

```latex
\documentclass[11pt]{article}
\usepackage[margin=1in]{geometry}
\usepackage{setspace}\onehalfspacing
\usepackage{graphicx}
\setlength{\parindent}{0pt}\setlength{\parskip}{0.5em}

\begin{document}

Dear [Editor First Name],

Thank you for the opportunity to review MS [number], ``[Paper Title].'' [1-2 sentences: what the paper studies, the method/data, the headline finding.]

I recommend \textbf{[rejection / major revisions / minor revisions / acceptance]} because [1-2 sentences integrating both contribution and methods perspectives. Reference key Deal Breakers if rejecting.]

I attach two detailed referee reports: one focused on the contribution and literature positioning, and one focused on research design and methodology. [Optional: 1 sentence highlighting the most critical issue if relevant.]

I hope these comments are useful.

Sincerely,

\vspace{-0.5em}
\includegraphics[width=2in]{Lulu_Wang_Signature.jpg}
\vspace{-0.5em}

Lulu Wang

\end{document}
```

**Copy signature image:** Before compiling, copy `Lulu_Wang_Signature.jpg` from `referee/components/` to the output directory.

